content.description:
Self Evident is an arete problem that requires a decent amount of problem solving and technical footwork.

Sit start at the arete with a left hand, horizontal crimp and a right hand, sloping bump. From there, gain a right hand pinch, stay tight (dab potential), reach a left hand crimp (crux), then finish up the remaining jugs and arete for the topout.

It may or may not be an issue, but the apex of the boulder is completely sound, just be aware of it.
content.protection: A pad or two, but the landing is very good.
content.location: This ascends the southeast arete of Entrada Rock.

content.description:
Do Not Resuscitate climbs a slight overhang on great edges. The problem is a cruise once through the difficult start move.

Sit start with an incut, left hand edge and a right hand sidepull/undercling. From there, make a big pull up to a left hand edge, follow with a better edge with the right, then reach the jug, and top it out left of the apex just right of the tree branches.

It may or may not be an issue, but the apex of the boulder is completely sound, just be aware of it.
content.protection: A pad should do it, the landing is good.
content.location: It climbs the south face of Entrada Rock.
